title: cargo doc crash on `narwhal-dag`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code ```bash git clone https://github.com/MystenLabs/sui.git cd sui git checkout devnet cd crates/sui-sdk cargo doc ``` ### Meta crash on 1.65, 1.66 and nightly `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (cc47b0699 2023-01-08) binary: rustc commit-hash: cc47b069983292e4ee8982d5dabe6301452c5f25 commit-date: 2023-01-08 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Unexpected result when selecting node_dag::NodeDag Obligation(predicate=Binder(ProjectionPredicate(AliasTy { substs: [T, Const { ty: usize, kind: Value(Leaf(0x0000000000000020)) }], def_id: DefId(45:903 ~ fastcrypto[3b71]::hash::Hash::TypedDigest), _use_mk_alias_ty_instead: () }, Term::Ty(_)), []), depth=2)', compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/auto_trait.rs:757:33 ```
